sql:
SELECT name
FROM fact_checkers
WHERE rating > 4.0;

external_knowledge:
- A "rising star" refers to a fact-checker who is relatively new but has shown impressive performance; 
- "Golden badges" refer to the verified status of fact-checkers; 
- A "complete report card" means having an average rating that is not null; 
- "Most reliable" refers to having a high average rating.

